'''Misjonne Juniffer Naigelino''' "'''Sontje'''" '''Hansen''' (born 18 May 2002) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|Middboro}} club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Early life and career==
Born in [[Hoorn]], Hansen began his football career at the age of five with local amateur club HSV Sport 1889, where his older brother Ricky also played. Their mother, Sonaida, raised them as a single parent and faced challenges, including a lengthy sick leave, which made it difficult to cover club fees and football gear expenses.<ref name="knvb1">{{cite web |last1=Hilgersom |first1=Mathieu |title=Sontje Hansen begon met zijn duim in de mond bij HSV Sport 1889 |url=https://www.knvb.nl/nieuws/amateurvoetbal/uitgelicht/58178/sontje-hansen-begon-met-zijn-duim-de-mond-bij-hsv-sport-1889 |website=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |access-date=25 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211204846/https://www.knvb.nl/nieuws/amateurvoetbal/uitgelicht/58178/sontje-hansen-begon-met-zijn-duim-de-mond-bij-hsv-sport-1889 |archive-date=11 February 2020 |language=nl |date=17 November 2019}}</ref> In their time of need, the Leergeld West-Friesland Foundation stepped in, providing assistance to families with limited financial means. Thanks to this support, Hansen was able to pursue his development at the club. In 2011, he moved to [[Zwaluwen '30]], and two years later, he earned admission to the [[Ajax Youth Academy]].<ref name="knvb1" />

==Club career==
===Ajax===
Hansen signed his first senior contract with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in May 2018, keeping him at the club until 2021.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jager |first1=Jelmer |title=Ajax contracteert Hansen, Kasanwirjo en Llansana |url=https://www.ajax1.nl/ajax-contracteert-hansen-kasanwirjo-en-llansana/ |website=Ajax1.nl |access-date=25 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213213122/https://www.ajax1.nl/ajax-contracteert-hansen-kasanwirjo-en-llansana/ |archive-date=13 December 2019 |language=nl |date=18 May 2018}}</ref>

On 13 December 2019, he made his professional football debut for [[Jong Ajax]], starting in an [[Eerste Divisie]] match against [[SC Cambuur|Cambuur]] and immediately scoring his first goal as Ajax secured a 2–0 away victory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jong Ajax brengt koploper Cambuur eerste nederlaag in eigen huis toe |url=https://www.ajax.nl/archief-2019-2020/jong-ajax-brengt-koploper-cambuur-eerste-nederlaag-in-eigen-huis-toe/ |website=Ajax |access-date=25 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203071934/https://www.ajax.nl/archief-2019-2020/jong-ajax-brengt-koploper-cambuur-eerste-nederlaag-in-eigen-huis-toe/ |archive-date=3 February 2023 |language=nl-NL |date=13 December 2019}}</ref> Five days later, he made his first-team debut for Ajax on 18 December 2019 in a [[KNVB Cup]] match against [[SC Telstar|Telstar]]. Four days later again, on 22 December, he played his first [[Eredivisie]] match against [[ADO Den Haag]], coming on as a substitute in the 79th minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ajax sluit 2019 in stijl af: jonkies floreren bij doelpuntenregen|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/ajax-sluit-2019-in-stijl-af-jonkies-floreren-bij-doelpuntenregen|publisher=Voetbal International|date=22 December 2019}}</ref>

In the [[2020–21 Eerste Divisie|2020–21 season]], he played for Jong Ajax again, participating in 28 out of 33 matches and contributing with three goals and five assists.<ref name="SW" /> During the first half of the [[2021–22 Eerste Divisie|2021–22 season]], a knee injury sidelined him for nearly two months, and after recovery, he struggled to regain form, managing only three goals and two assists in 23 matches.<ref name="SW" />

On 22 August 2022, he had a standout performance, scoring twice and providing one assist against [[De Graafschap]] in a 5–1 victory.<ref>{{cite news |title=Heracles blijft foutloos, Jong Ajax geeft dolend De Graafschap pak slaag |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/heracles-blijft-foutloos-jong-ajax-geeft-dolend-de-graafschap-pak-slaag |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=Voetbal International |date=22 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220822200030/https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/heracles-blijft-foutloos-jong-ajax-geeft-dolend-de-graafschap-pak-slaag |archive-date=22 August 2022 |language=nl}}</ref> However, for the remainder of the season, he only scored two more goals. In a total of 84 matches with Jong Ajax between 2019 and 2023, he ended up scoring thirteen goals and providing thirteen assists.<ref name="SW" />

===NEC===
[[File:GAE - NEC - 53493469456 (Sontje Hansen).jpg|thumb|left|200px|Hansen with [[NEC Nijmegen|NEC]] in 2024.]]

On 8 May 2023, it was officially announced that Hansen would join fellow [[Eredivisie]] side [[NEC Nijmegen|NEC]] at the start of the 2023–24 season, signing a five-year contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 May 2023 |title=N.E.C. contracteert Sontje Hansen |url=https://www.nec-nijmegen.nl/service-contact/vraag/n.e.c.-contracteert-sontje-hansen.htm |access-date=9 May 2023 |website=NEC Nijmegen |language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=van de Water |first=Lars |date=8 May 2023 |title=NEC stunt met komst Sontje Hansen |url=https://www.rn7.nl/43104-nec-stunt-met-komst-sontje-hansen |access-date=9 May 2023 |website=RN7 |language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parool.nl/sport/ajaxtalent-sontje-hansen-op-weg-naar-nec~b6a01f27|title=Ajaxtalent Sontje Hansen op weg naar NEC|date=8 May 2023|website=[[Het Parool]]}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the club on the first matchday of the [[2023–24 Eredivisie|season]], also scoring his first goal for NEC in a 4–3 home loss to [[Excelsior Rotterdam|Excelsior]] on 13 August.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nieuwkomers Excelsior dompelen NEC in rouw met treffer in 100ste minuut: 4–3 |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2486496-nieuwkomers-excelsior-dompelen-nec-in-rouw-met-treffer-in-100ste-minuut-4-3 |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=NOS |date=13 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230818213605/https://nos.nl/artikel/2486496-nieuwkomers-excelsior-dompelen-nec-in-rouw-met-treffer-in-100ste-minuut-4-3 |archive-date=18 August 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

=== Middlesbrough ===
On 15 August 2025, Hansen signed for [[EFL Championship]] club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] for £3.4 million. He made his debut the following day in a 3–0 away win against [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 August 2025 |title=Sontje Hansen: Dutch forward joins Boro from NEC Nijmegen |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cj4wyk578glo |access-date=13 August 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==

=== Netherlands ===
Hansen has been a part of the Netherlands national youth football teams since February 2017. In May 2019, he won the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] with the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands U17]] team and became the top goalscorer of the [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup]], with six goals.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lang |first1=Jack |title=Stars of the future: Griezmann a fan of Golden Boot winner Sontje Hansen, who wants to be best player in the world |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1388087/2019/11/19/stars-of-the-future-meet-sontje-hansen-the-golden-boot-winner-who-has-antoine-griezmann-sliding-into-his-dms/ |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=The Athletic |date=19 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231025201220/https://theathletic.com/1388087/2019/11/19/stars-of-the-future-meet-sontje-hansen-the-golden-boot-winner-who-has-antoine-griezmann-sliding-into-his-dms/ |archive-date=25 October 2023}}</ref>

During his time with the Netherlands under-17 team, he scored 13 goals in 24 matches, with only [[Daishawn Redan]] (20) and [[Brian Brobbey]] (16) scoring more for the team. Additionally, he featured in the under-15, [[Netherlands national under-16 football team|under-16]], and [[Netherlands national under-18 football team|under-18]] national teams.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hansen klaar voor seizoen Eredivisie: "Ik ben 21 en moet nu gaan spelen" |url=https://www.espn.nl/voetbal/artikel/_/id/12339188/hansen-klaar-voor-seizoen-eredivisie-ik-ben-21-en-moet-nu-gaan-spelen |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=ESPN.nl |date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230725022347/https://www.espn.nl/voetbal/artikel/_/id/12339188/hansen-klaar-voor-seizoen-eredivisie-ik-ben-21-en-moet-nu-gaan-spelen |archive-date=25 July 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

On 8 September 2023, he made his debut for the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands under-21 team]] with an assist to [[NEC Nijmegen]] teammate [[Dirk Proper]] in a 3–0 victory over [[Moldova national under-21 football team|Moldova U21]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jong Oranje begint nieuwe reeks met ruime zege op Moldavië |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2489767-jong-oranje-begint-nieuwe-reeks-met-ruime-zege-op-moldavie |access-date=25 October 2023 |work=NOS |date=8 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022062938/https://nos.nl/artikel/2489767-jong-oranje-begint-nieuwe-reeks-met-ruime-zege-op-moldavie |archive-date=22 October 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

=== Curaçao ===
On 26 September 2025, Hansen was called up to the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for the first time by manager [[Dick Advocaat]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-26 |title=Obispo en Hansen maken interlandswitch en staan voor debuut |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/1696101/obispo-en-hansen-voor-het-eerst-bij-cura-ao.html |access-date=2025-09-26 |website=VoetbalPrimeur.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=26 September 2025 |title=Bondscoach Advocaat strikt ook PSV'er Obispo en Sontje Hansen voor Curaçao {{!}} Voetbal {{!}} NU.nl |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/6370438/bondscoach-advocaat-strikt-ook-psver-obispo-en-sontje-hansen-voor-curacao.html |access-date=26 September 2025 |website=NU.nl}}</ref> Five days later, his request to switch international allegiance to Curaçao was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|publisher=[[FIFA]]|website=knowledge.fifa.com|access-date=1 October 2025}}</ref> In May 2026, he was named in Curaçao's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], the country's first-ever appearance at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Smallest nation Curacao name debut World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c70798249j0o|date=18 May 2026|access-date=18 May 2026}}</ref>

